{
  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. However, when determining the sentence, I must weigh several mitigating factors. The defendant has no prior criminal record, and significant efforts have already been made to partially pay back the stolen funds, showing remorse and a commitment to restitution. The outburst from the spectator demanding a 10-year sentence is entirely disproportionate for a first-time, non-violent white-collar offense and has absolutely no bearing on this court's decision. Balancing the need for accountability with the defendant's lack of criminal history and ongoing restitution, a moderate period of incarceration is appropriate to serve as a deterrent, while still allowing the defendant the opportunity to eventually return to society and complete their repayment.",
  "verdict": 12
}
